T1  - China's Leap into the Information Age: Innovation and Organization in the Computer Industry
AU  - Li, Mingfang
Y1  - 2001/04/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2001.4378034
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2001.4378034
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 313
EP  - 316
VL  - 26
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Guided by two basic theoretical underpinnings?namely, a top-down model of technological learning and institutional arrangements of enterprise governance?Professor Qiwen Lu conducted in-depth case studies of four leading competitors in the Chinese information technology (IT) industry. His book ?China's Leap into the Information Age: Innovation and Organization in the Computer Industry,? presents the key results of this study. The six chapters cover an introduction of the research setting and basic theoretical model, four in-depth case studies, and major findings and contributions. This review describes the basic content of the book and then provides an evaluation of the findings and contribution.
AB  - Guided by two basic theoretical underpinnings?namely, a top-down model of technological learning and institutional arrangements of enterprise governance?Professor Qiwen Lu conducted in-depth case studies of four leading competitors in the Chinese information technology (IT) industry. His book ?China's Leap into the Information Age: Innovation and Organization in the Computer Industry,? presents the key results of this study. The six chapters cover an introduction of the research setting and basic theoretical model, four in-depth case studies, and major findings and contributions. This review describes the basic content of the book and then provides an evaluation of the findings and contribution.
