N2  - The book ?Cooperative Strategy: Economic, Business, and Organizational Issues,? edited by David O. Faulkner and Mark de Rond, is an eclectic collection of eighteen papers written by individuals widely considered to be leading scholars in their chosen areas of academic study. These chapters contain useful ideas and are well written. The credit for this goes to the individual authors, of course, but also to the volume's editors, who have done a remarkable job of organizing the authors' diverse perspectives into a five-part coherent whole.
